  <u>the day</u>
</b> finally arrives. <br/><br/>Even if Capote&apos;s Christmas is not your Christmas, and neither was it exactly my Christmas, because all of our Christmases are a little bit different from each other&apos;s, Capote magnificently captures what bubbles in our bodies and zings in our hearts at Christmas.<br/><br/>The ending has a hint of nostalgia which is perfect too.<br/><br/>Fantastic. Read it! Read it aloud </span>
