  <u>the day</u>
</b> finally arrives. <br /><br />Even if Capote's Christmas is not your Christmas, and neither was it exactly my Christmas, because all of our Christmases are a little bit different from each other's, Capote magnificently captures what bubbles in our bodies and zings in our hearts at Christmas.<br /><br />The ending has a hint of nostalgia which is perfect too.<br /><br />Fantastic. Read it! Read it aloud to others in your family. Turn this story into a family tradition. It's that good!<br /><br />Here I go again, giving a short little story five stars. <br /><br /><br />**********************************<br /><br />Here follows a free on-line link to this autobiographical short story:: <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://www.sailthouforth.com/2009/12/christmas-memory.html">http://www.sailthouforth.com/2009/12/...</a></span>
